                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>All miracles are numbered.</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Text I-2 includes the hymns:</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝl ba-kǝlʾe Māryām walādita ʾamlāk ... "O my Lady, Holy Two-fold Virgin Mary, Godbearing ..." (<locus from="9rb" to="9va">9rb-9va</locus> l.16)</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝl Māryām Mariham ʾǝmmu la-ʾIyasus Krǝstos kahāli ... "O my Lady, Holy Virgin Mary, Mother of Jesus Christ the Almighty ..." (<locus target="#9va">9va</locus> l.16-vb l.14)(cp. ChRep n<locus target="#373">373</locus>)</note>
                     <note>- salām laki ʾo-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝl Māryām ʾǝmma madḫǝn wa-ʾǝmma bǝrhān ... "Salutation to you, o my Lady, Holy Virgin Mary, Mother of the Saviour and Mother of the Light ..." (<locus target="#9vb">9vb</locus> l.14-10va)</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Text I-3 contains:</note>
                     <note>- Ṣalota za-yǝtbähal ʾǝmqǝdmä yanbǝbu täʾamriha la-ʾǝgzǝʾt kwǝllǝnä ... "Prayer recited before reading the Miracles of our Lady ..." (<locus from="11rb" to="12ra">11rb-12ra</locus>)</note>
                     <note>- Excerpt from the Gospel of John (Jn. 19:25-27) (<locus target="#12ra">12ra-</locus>rb).</note>
                  </msItem>
